{{Year in Wales header|2012}}
This article is about the particular significance of the year '''2012''' to [[Wales]] and [[Welsh people|its people]].

==Incumbents==
*[[Prince of Wales]] <U+2013> [[Charles, Prince of Wales|The Prince Charles]]
*[[Princess of Wales]] <U+2013> [[Camilla, Duchess of Cornwall|The Duchess of Cornwall]] (Camilla; does not use title)
*[[First Minister of Wales|First Minister]] <U+2013> [[Carwyn Jones]] AM 
*[[Presiding Officer of the National Assembly for Wales]] - [[Rosemary Butler (politician)|Rosemary Butler]]
*[[Secretary of State for Wales]] - [[Cheryl Gillan]]
*[[Archbishop of Wales]] <U+2013> [[Barry Morgan]]
*[[Archdruid]] of the [[National Eisteddfod of Wales]] <U+2013> [[T. James Jones|Jim Parc Nest]]

==Events==
*[[1 January]] - Welsh recipients of [[2012 New Year Honours|New Year Honours]] include musician Walford Hutchings, rugby player [[Martyn Williams]] and politician [[Alex Carlile, Baron Carlile of Berriew|Alex Carlile]].<ref>{{cite web|title=New Year Honours: Musician Walford Hutchings's MBE |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-wales-south-east-wales-16353246| |publisher=BBC: South East Wales| date=31 December 2011|accessdate=25 February 2012}}</ref>
*[[12 January]] - Controversial proposals for a new school "banding" system are unveiled by Assembly minister [[Leighton Andrews]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Ex-head hits out at school banding scoring system |url=http://www.walesonline.co.uk/cardiffonline/cardiff-news/2012/01/12/ex-head-hits-out-at-school-banding-scoring-system-91466-30106340/ |publisher=Wales Online |author=Brendan, Hughes |work=South Wales Echo |date=12 January 2012|accessdate=12 January 2012}}</ref>
*[[19 January]] - 249 staff at the Cardiff HQ of [[Peacocks (clothing)|Peacocks]] are made redundant as the company goes into administration.<ref>{{cite web|title=Peacocks administrators KPMG 'look for buyer' for clothing chain |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-wales-south-east-wales-16639166 |publisher=[[BBC News]]|date=20 January 2012|accessdate=25 February 2012}}</ref>
*[[27 January]] - It is revealed that the missing documents which caused the collapse of the [[Murder of Lynette White|Lynette White police corruption trial]] in November 2011 have been found.<ref>{{cite web|title=Lynette White police corruption acquittal: Retrial very unlikely, says QC |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-wales-south-east-wales-16757255 |publisher=[[BBC News]]|date=27 January 2012|accessdate=27 January 2012}}</ref>
*[[30 January]] - The inquest into the death of former Wales football manager [[Gary Speed]] returns a "narrative verdict".<ref>{{cite web|title=Gary Speed confided in friend Alan Shearer that there were 'issues' in his marriage months before he killed himself |url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2093792/Gary-Speed-inquest-Issues-marriage-Louise-months-suicide-Alan-Shearer-reveals.html| |publisher=Mail Online|title=Speed's memory 'shines brightly in our thoughts', in statement|author=Dolan, Andy; Cooper, Rob; Tozer, James | date=2 February 2012|accessdate=25 February 2012}}</ref>
*[[1 March]] - As part of [[Saint David's Day]] celebrations, the Welsh Assembly announces that the home of poet [[Hedd Wyn]] has been secured for the nation by the Snowdonia National Park Authority.<ref>{{cite web|title=Poet Hedd Wyn's home safe after Snowdonia authority takes ownership |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-wales-north-west-wales-17221011| |publisher=BBC News|author= | date=1 March 2012|accessdate=2 March 2012}}</ref>

