==Sport==
*[[Boxing]]
**[[25 February]] - [[Nathan Cleverly]] beats [[Tommy Karpency]] to retain his WBO light-heavyweight title.<ref>{{cite web|title=Nathan Cleverly holds on to world crown against Tommy Karpency |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/boxing/17169329 |publisher=BBC Sport|date=25 February 2012 |accessdate=26 February 2012}}</ref>

*[[Association football|Football]]
**[[19 January]] - [[Chris Coleman (footballer)|Chris Coleman]] is appointed as the manager of the [[Wales national football team|Wales national team]].<ref>{{cite web|title='I'll carry on Gary's work,' says new Wales boss Coleman in pitch perfect speech |url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2088833/Chris-Coleman-replaces-Gary-Speed-Wales-manager.html |author=Moxley, Neil|publisher=Mail Online|date=20 January 2012 |accessdate=25 February 2012}}</ref>
**[[26 February]] - [[Cardiff City F.C.|Cardiff City]] are beaten by [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]] in the [[2012 Football League Cup Final]], the game ending on penalties when the score finished 2-2 after extra time.<ref>{{cite web|title=Kenny Dalglish believes Carling Cup win can inspire Liverpool |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/17174308 |author=Bevan, Chris |publisher=BBC Sport|date=26 February 2012 |accessdate=26 February 2012}}</ref>

*[[Rugby union]]
**[[25 February]] - In the [[2012 Six Nations Championship]], [[Wales national rugby union team|Wales]] beat [[England national rugby union team|England]] at Twickenham to take their 20th [[Triple Crown (rugby union)|Triple Crown]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Six Nations: England 12-19 Wales |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/rugby-union/17141687 |author=Fordyce, Tom| publisher=[[BBC Sport]]|date=25 February 2012|accessdate=25 February 2012}}</ref>

*[[Snooker]]
**[[Ding Junhui]] wins the [[2012 Welsh Open (snooker)|2012 Welsh Open]] by defeating [[Mark Selby]] 9<U+2013>6 in the final.<ref>{{cite web|title=Welsh Open: China's Ding Junhui beats Mark Selby 9<U+2013>6 to lift title|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/snooker/17091924 |publisher=[[BBC Sport]]|date=19 February 2012|accessdate=25 February 2012}}</ref>

